    UCRM API

    Introduction

    Authentication

    In order to use this API, you will need an app key.

    Generating an App Key

    Go to App keys (Settings => Security => App keys) section of your UCRM instance and generate a new app key of required type (Read or Write).

    Request Method Type
    GET Read, Write
    POST Write
    PUT Write
    PATCH Write
    DELETE Write

    Using an App Key

    Once you have generated an app key, pass it in X-Auth-App-Key header in each request.

    If an app key is not passed or invalid, you will get a 401 Unauthorized response. If an app key is of wrong type, you will get a 403 Forbidden response.
